news.title: Greenlighting construction in buffer zones in Bengaluru illegal: Experts
news.para: Amid the assurance by deputy chief minister DK Shivakumar that citizens owning plots in buffer zones around forest areas on the city’s outskirts will be allowed to construct buildings, legal experts and forest officials say the move will pave the way for a bitter confrontation.

news.title: Has the licence for lift in your flat, building in Kochi been renewed?
news.para: While this is undoubtedly a cause for concern, as per the data from four fire stations in the city, as many as 15 incidents of people getting stuck in lifts were reported in the past eight months this year.

news.title: DDA nudges landowners to opt for land pooling policy, finds few takers
news.para: Delhi's land pooling policy of 2018 aims to develop 105 villages that are divided into five zones - P-II, K-I, L, N and J. The land pooling, to be done by land owners through a consortium, requires 70% of the required land to be contiguous and without encumbrances.
